dare, Ireland","County Limerick, Ireland":"County Limerick, Ireland","Thomond Manor, Connaught Bridge, Kildare, Leinster, Ireland":"Connaught Bridge, County Kildare, Ireland","Limerick, Ireland":"County Limerick, Ireland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"O'Brien","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Dermot, Liam, Brigid, Declan, Donovan, John Patrick, Kieran, Colm, Donal, Brennan, Caitlin.","Irish: Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Ó Briain</b> ‘descendant of <i>Brian</i>’, a personal name probably based on the element <i>bre-</i> ‘hill’, with the transferred sense ‘eminence’, i.e. ‘exalted one’. See also   Bryan  . In Ireland there has also been some confusion with   O'Byrne   (see   Byrne  ).","History: This name is borne in particular by one of the greatest of Irish septs, descendants of Brian Boru, who rose to the high kingship of Ireland in 1002."],"variants":[{"name":"O'Brion","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryon","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish William Kevin.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"Bryan","meanings":["English and Irish: variant of   Bryant  .","Irish: shortened Anglicized form of <b>Ó Briain</b>, see   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Briant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  , with excrescent <i>-t</i>."]},{"name":"O'Bryant","meanings":["Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"McBrien","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Brendan, Seamus.","Irish:","Anglicized form of Gaelic <b>Mac Briain</b> ‘son of Brian’. See   O'Brien   and   Bryan  ."]},{"name":"O'Brian","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish Liam.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]},{"name":"O'Bryan","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Irish James Patrick, Padraic.","Irish: variant of   O'Brien  ."]}]},{"name":"Mahon","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Fla